{
  "text": "By considering the development of the signal amplitude and the simultaneous change in shape to lower energies in the real-valued 2D spectra in figure 3 , the relaxation process is also evident. Besides the simple overall relaxation observable in all spectra into the lower Q-band [CITATION_1] (as also known for similar systems [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ) which manifests itself only indirectly in this study, since then no SE from S 2 is possible anymore, the signal amplitude for high excitation\u03bd \u03c4 and low detection\u03bd t wavenumbers changes with time. This indicates a relaxation by solvent effects such as a Stokes shift or by a population transfer from |\u03b2 to |\u03b1 , as the change mainly appears as an off-diagonal signal between the corresponding excitonic states.",
